creator: Anne Brontë
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 15 recordings of The Captive Dove by Anne Bronte. This was the Weekly Poetry project for January 17, 2016. Read in English by Aubrey Anne; Bruce Kachuk; Brian Darby; clarinetcarrot; David J. Heaney; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Jennifer Fournier; Gloria Fontaine; Greg Giordano; John Burlinson; Julia Niedermaier; Lee Ann Howlett; Maria Kasper and Rapunzelina. Many victorian women felt trapped by the role society gave them. So did Anne Bronte. This is a poem about lonelyness, and about feeling caged. A poem which would bring tears to your eyes. ( Stav Nisser ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
